  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">This is a reply to Alfred H. Love&apos;s invitation to give a lecture a few days before the opening of the decade anniversary celebration (of the American Anti-Slavery Society) in Philadelphia. William Lloyd Garrison cheerfully agrees to give the lecture provided J. M. M&apos;Kim agrees to lecture. Garrison would like to read Alfred H. Love&apos;s statement relative to being drafted &quot;and declining to pay the $300 commutative alternative.&quot; Garrison elaborates on this: &quot;I think the money can be paid without any compromise of the peace or non-resistance principles; but if you do not, (and in a matter like this, everyone will do well, and best, to be fully persuaded in his own mind,) you must be true to your own convictions.&quot;</subfield>
  </datafield>
